                    <span class="tag-accessibility">Accessibility</span>
                </div>
                <div class="card-header collaboration-header">
                    <h3 class="featured-title">Collaborative Health Education</h3>
                    <p class="featured-subtitle">Project Assistant (UDL)</p>
                </div>
                <div class="card-content">
                    <h4 class="project-title">Advancing Accessible Interprofessional Education</h4>
                    <p class="project-description">
                        In 2025, I worked with UBC Health as Lead Developer on curriculum materials and visuals reaching 2,000+ students across 14 health programs. I collaborated with faculty, clinicians, and institutional stakeholders to engineer interprofessional workshops on ethics, health informatics, and collaborative decision-making, improving accessibility, cultural sensitivity, and learner engagement. I co-authored the UBC Health Facilitator Guide, developed a simplified, icon-based version of the CIHC Competency Framework, and served as French Language Editor for its Référentiel des compétences, strengthening the national bilingual standard.
                    </p>
                    <span class="project-link">FORTHCOMING PUBLICATIONS IN PROGRESS</span>
